title: Nusa Penida by Speed Boat (Snorkeling & Manta Rays)
description: Travel in style to Nusa Penida in a private boat (not public ferry) accompanied by an English-speaking guide. This is a shared, small group tour with max capacity of 13 people. Swimming with Giant Manta Rays, snorkeling in 4 spots by Nusa Penida and Lembongan!. Explore Kelingking cliff car tour (if have enough time we can see Broken Beach and Angel’s Billabong). Enjoy scenic lunch with views and infinity pool access. Secure underwater photos and video with no extra charge. Try an upgrade to our Premium Shared Tour that includes a prmium boat, pro-photographer, welcome drinks and juices, two complimentary bottles of prosecco.

title: Blue Lagoon Snorkeling in Bali with Optional Activities & Tour
description: Book through Klook and visit two of the best snorkeling areas on the beautiful island of Bali!. The Blue Lagoon and Tanjung Jepun are great snorkeling spots for beginners because of their calm waters. Take a refreshing dip into these two water wonderlands and discover a variety of underwater treasure. Marvel at the majestic, tropical marine life and befriend cuttlefish, angelfish, cowfish, and even moray eels!. Combine your snorkeling trip with exploring Ubud Monkey Forest, Tegalalang Rice Terraces & Bali-Waterfalls. Enjoy a half-day tour to Pura Lempuyang and Tirta Gangga (optional add-on)

title: Devdan Show Ticket in Bali
description: Experience Indonesian “Unity in Diversity” as you watch performances from the many cultures spread across the islands, including Bali, Sumatra, Java, Kalimantan, Papua, and more!. See this award winning production on Indonesian culture, the top rated show for visitors to Indonesia. Watch a fusion of modern elements like acrobatics and special effects which will keep you on the edge of your seat!. Witness a mesmerizing collaboration genre of Indonesia folk and contemporary dance

title: Water World Ocean Park Hong Kong Ticket
description: Discover Water World -- Asia's first all-weather, year-round waterfront water park. Just minutes from the urban center, prepare to enter a mystical, hidden civilisation at one with the wonders of water and nature. The Water World looks forward to hosting you in our secret world of water, and embark on an exciting adventure in the five unique zones. Come escape the heat at Water World with its wave pools, rivers and thrilling slides. Set where lush mountains meet the South China Sea, Water World's architecture which respects the unique landscape and Environmentally-conscious design & details, encourage adventurers to embrace the importance of preserving it

title: Hong Kong Palace Museum Ticket
description: Located at the western tip of the West Kowloon Cultural District, The Hong Kong Palace Museum presents several hundred priceless treasures from the Palace Museum. Many of them are on display in Hong Kong for the first time, while others have never been shown to the public before. Embracing new curatorial approaches, the Museum will offer a Hong Kong perspective and a global vision, and regularly presents special exhibitions featuring Chinese art and culture, as well as art and treasures from other parts of the world.
